data.name: cb_ParamDetail.ToolTip
data.value:
Parameter List - selects the parameter to be set:
Start / End Detail Page : Permet de réduire le code source à la section qui nous intéresse. Original Title : Titre original. Translated Title : Titre traduit. URL cover : URL de l'affiche. Rate 1 : Note 1. Rate 2 : Note 2. Description / Synopsys : Description of film Director: Director (s) Producer: Producer (s) Actors: Actors Country: Country Genre: Genre/Categories. Year: Year. URL Redirection cover: For posters better, it is sometimes need to click on another tab. This setting allows you to find in the code address tab. Then use Start / End cover to find the URL address of the poster in this new page. URL Redirection common: Redirection for common pupose Comment: Comment or user review Language: Language Tagline: Tagline Certification: Certification

data.name: TextKeyStartD.ToolTip
data.value:
String that defines the beginning of the parameter.
SpecialParameters for beginning of expression: "normal" : Find last index pf parameter "#REGEX#" (KEYSTART/END / PARAM1/2): Find first/last with Regex "#REVERSE#" (PARAM1/2): Reverse search

data.name: TextKeyStopD.ToolTip
data.value:
String that defines the end of the parameter.
SpecialParameters for beginning of expression: "normal" : Find last index pf parameter "#REGEX#" (KEYSTART/END / PARAM1/2): Find first/last with Regex "#REVERSE#" (PARAM1/2): Reverse search

data.name: textComplement.ToolTip
data.value: Different meanings: Rating: Allows to clarify more precisely the basis of the score (Score 5, 10, 20 ...) Others: Allows regex expressions to get content as matchgroups. #MULTILINE# allows to perform regex match collection with multiline regexoption. Default is "Singleline". Match Groups: To enable the usage of "match groups", in "Replace" field you have to use "#REGEX#". No parameters are required, but this will enable the scraper engine to use match groups when getting data.

data.name: textDReplace.ToolTip
data.value:
This area of the right will replace a string parameter by another.
Use the "paramter Preview" to see the result.
#REGEX# - supports regex for cleanup #MULTI# - supports multiple replacements - separated by ";" and "|" - e.g. "#MULTI#the|the ;movie|m" #REGEX##MULTI# - supports multiple replacements as regex - format as with #MULTI#
#ADD# - supports adding characters at start and end of result. Using "|" as separator allows to add different characters at start and end. Set Characters to add in "With" field.

data.name: Index.ToolTip
data.value: This can be useful in cases where it is impossible to find one key in the code. The grabber will therefore seek the chain starting from the last parameter instead of starting from the beginning of the code.

data.name: textLanguages.ToolTip
data.value:
Enter the language, as stated on the website you use to get languagespecific details. Example: Translated titel on IMDB: Set Language(s) to "Germany" to get the german translated title.
Remarks: - Only works in Regex Mode - You can enter more than 1 language to get results for several lnaguages listed - Translated Title and Certification support language filtered results - to get such results, the web page you use must return the naguage string with your group matching expression. - Matching is based on "parially contains" - so defining e.g. "german" would also return all values that have "Germany".

data.name: textLanguagesAll.ToolTip
data.value: You can define here what Countries/Languages will be available in Dropdownbox on "User Options" tab.

data.value: Loads the source code for the url.

data.name: button_Find_Detail.ToolTip
data.value: Seeking a string in the source code. Pressing multiple times jumps to the next found position. If end of code is reached, it will restart from the beginning with searching.

data.name: buttonPreviewDetailFullGrab.ToolTip
data.value: Preview the result of the grabber settings. If it contains a cover image, it will be shown in preview box. This preview takes all user settings into consideration.

data.name: buttonPrevParamDetail.ToolTip
data.value: Show the result of current setting. If the result is an Image, it will be shown in the preview box. preview page param does not use all "user settings" - to check if all options are working as desired, please use "Preview Full Grab".

data.name: lblResult.ToolTip
data.value: This shows the result after you klicked "preview parameter". If result is a URL, you can load it into the windows to define rules. Thus is usable when defining rules on "secondary pages" like Image Link URL.

data.name: TextURL.ToolTip
data.value:
URL of the search page.
On that site, search with a keyword relevant (eg "black"), to get many results. Some sites offer first a little list of results sorted by categories with a link "more results" for example. That's what you need to copy link: results will be more and especially the page will be easier to cut. (1 class only).
Important: You must replace the search string that you used with the string # # Search in the url and the page number from page # # (if present).
If you want to define a local grabber (nfo, xbmc, local html, text or xml files), you have to use "#Filename#" in the search definition. This will be replaced by the grabber engine with the name of the mediafile.

data.name: cb_Parameter.ToolTip
data.value:
Parameter list.
With the exception of "Start / End Result List," all parameters reported for 1 and 1 single result list.
Start / End Result List: Not mandatory, but strongly recommended! it reduces the source code to have that part of the results. Start / End Title: Required. Start / End Year: Not required. Start / End Director: Not required. Start / End Detail Page URL: Required.
Important: When defining grab areas, make sure, either URL or title are starting "earliest" - as otherwise the other parameters might not be grabbed properly anymore due to "lowest start value" being too high ...

data.value: Keyword search Two cases are supported: 1. internet search: If "Search" is part of the search definition 2. local search: If #Filename# is part of the search definition

data.name: cbTtitlePreferredLanguage.ToolTip
data.value: You can set the preferred language for the seconfor secondary title. THis is only useful, if the site is providing/supporting more than 1 language - plus the grabber script has to support them too via regex grouping. You can add multiple languages, if you want the grabber to get more than one title on supported sites/scripts.

data.name: groupBox8.ToolTip
data.value: Might be translated title, AKA title, depending on website...

data.name: dataGridViewMapping.ToolTip
data.value:
With the Mapping Table you can control the mapping of grabbed data to your catalog fields. You can e.g. map data of fields, that are missing in your catlaog to an existing field. You can "merge" data by adding it to fields at the end or the beginning. Options: - Replace: replaces the content of the destionation field with content of source field - Add to Start: Adds the content of source to the beginning of the destination field - Add to End: Adds the content of source to the end of the destination field - Merge (prefer source): replaces the content of the destionation field with content of source field, if source is not empty - Merge (prefer destination): replaces the content of the destionation field with content of source field, if destination is not empty
Note: You can add more than one field to a destination field - so you could e.g. merge data from several source fields to a single destination field.

data.name: groupBox10.ToolTip
data.value: IMDB offers "Certifiaction" for different countries. You can either leave the field empty to get all or define some countries (more than one possible) to get those specitic certifications. This feature only works, if the script and the web site supports it. Most sites do not support country specific certifications.

data.name: URLpage.ToolTip
data.value: Select the page you want to load data from. base or empty is the base details page. You can specify sub urls to load data based on more detailed sub pages or even other pages (like OFDB) sub pages can be cascaded, but order must be as listed here to make sure, data of referenced page is already loded / grabbed.

data.name: textFind.ToolTip
data.value: Expression to search. Support normal and gergex search. to make a regex search, add "#REGEX#" at the start of the expression.

data.name: textBox5.ToolTip
data.value: Expression to search. Support normal and gergex search. to make a regex search, add "#REGEX#" at the start of the expression.

data.name: textboxSearchAkasRegex.ToolTip
data.value: Define a regex matchgroup collection to add additional titles to the match results. Those will be used for matching in MF and AMCupdater. Example: aka.\"(?<aka>.*?)\" Note: The group definition "(?<aka>.*?)" must always be present to properly collect title infos.

data.name: button_openMediafile.ToolTip
data.value: If you define a local grabber, you can browse to open a media file. This is only useful, if you have "#Filename#" in your search definition, otherwise the internet database would get this media file name as search expression.

data.name: textEncoding.ToolTip
data.value:
manually override Encoding setting. Normally can be empty, as webgrabber automatically detects the encoding based on the web content.
Most common example: A website requiring UTF-8 Encoding: "UTF-8".

data.name: textLanguage.ToolTip
data.value: language(s) supported by the grabber script. usage: - 2-letter langiage - "|" or comma as separator - "all" or "*" for all languages

data.name: textType.ToolTip
data.value: Type of grabber script. usage: - "|" or comma as separator - "details", "cover", "fanart" as possible values - "covers", "photos", "trailers", "personimages"

data.name: textVersion.ToolTip
data.value: Version of the grabber script, e.g. "1.3"

data.name: textSearchCleanup.ToolTip
data.value: Cleaup: For certain websites, you need some sort of cleanup to remove certain characters from searchtitle (e.g. MoviePilot doesn't accept "-" char in search). This field allows you to "clean" your search expression.

data.name: textDReplaceWith.ToolTip
data.value: This is normally the replacement string. Under special conditions, there is command allowed too: When using regex match groups, the cleanup via "Replace" is done with hardcoded With = "" and only applying to the inner matchgroup strings. In that case, you can define cleanup commands for the outer results here: Supported commands: #REGEX# (for cleanup of outer result) #REGEX##MULTI# for multiple replacements (see "Replace") To use a linebreak, use #LF# - this will internally be cahnged into a linebreak. Example: #REGEX##MULTI#, |#LF# will replace comma separated results with linebreaked results.

data.name: textAccept.ToolTip
data.value: Optional: Can define the accept for the webrequest - required by some websites. Example: Request.Accept = "image/gif, image/x-xbitmap, image/jpeg, image/pjpeg, application/vnd.ms-excel, application/vnd.ms-powerpoint, application/msword, application/x-shockwave-flash, */*";

data.name: textUserAgent.ToolTip
data.value: Optional: Can define the useragent for the webrequest - required by some websites. Example: Request.UserAgent = "Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.2; SV1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; InfoPath.1)";

data.name: textHeaders.ToolTip
data.value: Optionsl: Adds headres to the webrequest - required by some websites. Multiple headers can be added by separating headres with "|" name/value for each header will be separated by "|". Example: Value "Accept-Language|ru###Accept-Encoding|deflate,sdch" will result in Request.Headers.Add("Accept-Language", "ru"); Request.Headers.Add("Accept-Encoding", "deflate,sdch");

If you want to create a new configuration based on the existing script, you can edit and then save it to another name ("Save As ...").
